{{Infobox football biography |name = Cheong Hoi San |image = |caption = |fullname = |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1998|06|26|df=y}} |birth_place = |height = {{height|m=}} |currentclub = [[MFA Development]] |clubnumber = 18 |position = [[Midfielder]] |youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = |years1 = 2015 |clubs1 = [[Hong Ngai]] |caps1 = |goals1 = |years2 = 2016 |clubs2 = [[Windsor Arch Ka I]] |caps2 = 0 |goals2 = 0 |years3 = 2016– |clubs3 = [[MFA Development]] |caps3 = 7 |goals3 = 2 |nationalyears1 = 2016 |nationalteam1 = [[Macau national under-19 football team|Macau U19]] |nationalcaps1 = 3 |nationalgoals1 = 0 |nationalyears2 = 2016–2018 |nationalteam2 = [[Macau national under-23 football team|Macau U23]] |nationalcaps2 = 5 |nationalgoals2 = 0 |nationalyears3 = 2015– |nationalteam3 = [[Macau national football team|Macau]] |nationalcaps3 = 12 |nationalgoals3 = 0 |club-update = 23:53, 25 March 2017 (UTC) |nationalteam-update = 19:12, 14 September 2018 (UTC) }}
'''Cheong Hoi San''' (born 26 June 1998) is a Macanese international [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for the [[MFA Development]] and the [[Macau national football team]].
==International career== Cheong was called up to the Macau senior team in February 2015 in preparation for [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC First Round|2018 FIFA World Cup qualification]] games,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.macaodaily.com/html/2015-02/04/content_972192.htm |title=澳足備戰世盃外圍賽 |date=4 February 2017 |accessdate=26 March 2017 |work=Macau Daily |language=Cantonese}}</ref> but would have to wait until November of the same year for his debut, which came against [[Hong Kong national football team|Hong Kong]] in a 2-0 defeat. He played in a 3-1 win over the [[Northern Mariana Islands national football team|Northern Mariana Islands]] in 2016, coming on as a 90th-minute substitute for [[Chan Man]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eaff.com/competitions/eaff2017r1/result205.html |title=Northern Mariana Islands 1-3 Macau |date=2 July 2016 |accessdate=26 March 2017 | work=EAFF}}</ref>
==Career statistics==
