{{infobox country at games | NOC = GRN | NOCname = Grenada Olympic Committee | games = Summer Olympics | year = 2004 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.grenadaolympic.com }} | location = [[Athens]] | competitors = '''5''' | sports = 2 | flagbearer = [[Alleyne Francique]] | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = 1984 | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Grenada]]''' competed at the '''[[2004 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Athens]], [[Greece]], from 13 to 29 August 2004. This was the nation's sixth consecutive appearance at the Olympics.
Grenada Olympic Committee sent a total of five athletes (three men and two women), competing only in athletics and swimming. Track runner and world indoor champion [[Alleyne Francique]] was appointed by the committee to become the nation's flag bearer in the opening ceremony.<ref>{{cite news|title=2004 Athens: Flag Bearers for the Opening Ceremony|url=http://www.olympic.org/content/news/media-resources/manual-news/1999-2009/2004/08/13/flag-bearers-for-the-opening-ceremony/|publisher=[[Olympics]]|date=13 August 2004|accessdate=11 September 2013}}</ref> A top favorite in the men's 400 metres, Francique narrowly missed a chance to grab the nation's first ever Olympic medal with a fantastic fourth-place finish.<ref>{{cite news|title=Wariner wins 400m final|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/olympics_2004/athletics/3592420.stm|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=23 August 2004|accessdate=4 April 2014}}</ref>
